      "content": "i mean i get that some people argue that, but isn't it also true that a stronger safety net can actually help people find better, more stable jobs because they aren't just desperate for anything? like it can actually improve workforce quality in the long run. why does it seem like you're mostly focusing on the negative side of the argument?",
